Hostile Terrain 94 is a participatory exhibition created by the Undocumented Migration Project, a non-profit organization that focuses on the social process of immigration and raises awareness through research, education, and outreach. The exhibit is composed of 3,992 handwritten toe tags representing migrants who died trying to cross the Sonoran Desert from the mid-1990s to 2023. Visit the Grinnell College Hostile Terrain 94 website for more information: ht94.sites.grinnell.edu


